2022 we had some good times! Lots of time well spent behind the easel, pushing shapes and colors to new heights. I’m really looking forward to what 2023 has in store for our little Melty family. Cheers to y’all.

“Mountain Loops” 16x20 oil on canvas.  Available and currently on display at @phillewisart  gallery in Boulder, CO. This weekend is your last chance to go check out the show in person if you’re in the Boulder / Denver area. Thanks again to everyone that came by the opening 💜 The amount of support and general stoke for my art is incredible and I appreciate y’all so much! 🫠🤙

“Melt into the Mountain” 11x14 oil on canvas. 
This painting started as a late night IG Live painting that I just kept noodling on in the studio. It evolved into this story in my head of these people gazing upon these odd monolithic heads melting into the southwestern landscape for no reason at all. Come to think of it, most the time my art is about the nonsense. And for the most part this whole existence is all nonsense isn’t it 🫠 it makes no sense 🫠 but damn it’s pretty in its own weird little way 🌵
This painting is available - mrmelty.com

Oh SNAP!! Forgot to post a pic of this piece I started at @hogfarmhideaway !! Got a ways to go with this one but thought I’d share. 
I had such a wonderful time in California last month!  New friendships forged and old friendships rekindled, so hard to put down into words how much you all mean to me. 

This life we live isn’t easy and it isn’t always Sunshines and rainbows, but damn when that sunshine hits your blood, it’s pretty damn good.  I want to show my gratitude to all the people in my life that have helped lift me up along the way to pursue art as my journey. Without you it’s hard to say where I’d be today.  Support is everything and I really hope that you feel that love in return.  I want the best for all y’all and to lift you up as much as I can anyway I can. 

Keep on crushing team! We got a long life to live and a lot of love to give.  See ya round the bend 🫶

@secretdreamsfest you have my heart and my silly little soul 🌀 cheers to everyone that made that possible! New friends and old💗 I love you! Always good to see you. Big thanks to @gavinger_  and @thegallerysociety and everyone that worked so hard in the gallery to sell some art and get us there.  And Mark and Erin from @nomadic_movement  I love y’all so much and cheers to a successful first drop with y’all. Cheers to anyone that scooped up a hoodie and joggers!  They came out so fire!!And big ups to my boss ass babe wife @taemissmess for helping me get everything together to make this trip a breeeze!  So much happens behind the scenes to make everything come together it’s really amazing to see it all unfold into a magical weekend. And it’s so gratifying to see people enjoy the fruits of our labor and to really inspire folks to live a more creative and colorful life everyday.  I feel like we’re at the culmination of the summer festivals and we all brought our A-Game!  I can only hope I get to be a part of this festival again in the future. With all that being said. It feels so damn good to be in bed with my dogs and my boo.  Until next time Ohio. 
I love you ❤️🫠❤️

Heyo! It’s time I put some of my new pieces up in the online shop🫠 This past summer (into the very short NM fall) was a wild one for the Melty’s! Between all the festivals, art shows, weddings and bachelor parties I hadn’t had much time to myself. It was time for me to lay low and set my controls for new horizons. So that’s what I’ve been up to lately, working on my house/yard, gathering inspiration for new projects and creating new designs for new merch. A solid reset 🙌🏼 Stoked for what’s to come. 

I haven’t posted much of the art I’ve created in the past couple months but I’ve started to put a couple new originals in my online shop. These Melty Originals 🌵💀🌵are 12x24 acrylic on canvas and looking for new homes!!!
